description:
Two young women disappear in the Panamanian jungle...what happened to Kris Kremers and Lisanne Froon? In this video, we break down the chilling timeline of their disappearance, examine the haunting photos taken during their final days, debunk persistent rumors, and explore the leading theories behind this tragic case. Well also look at the investigation, unanswered questions, and the evidence that continues to baffle experts. This is one of the most mysterious true crime cases I've covered to date.

The content in this video is for informational and educational purposes only. Nothing I say should be interpreted as legal advice, medical advice, or professional counseling of any kind.
The views presented are opinion-based and explore criminal actions, true crime, deception detection, body language analysis, ideas, arguments, and perspectives. Nothing stated is conclusive; everything is speculative. I do not endorse a particular stance regarding these ideas, nor do I endorse a particular outcome of this case or trial. 

All references to laws, cases, historical events, and philosophical arguments are accurate to the best of my research at the time of publication, but laws change, and information evolves, so always do your own due diligence.

Sources used to collect all information in this video include various public news sites, interviews, court documents, FB groups dedicated to the case, and news channel segments. When quoting statements made by others, they are strictly alleged until confirmed otherwise. 

Comments on this channel are the sole responsibility of their writers. Therefore, the writers take full responsibility, liability, and blame for any libel or litigation that results from something written in or as a direct result of something written in a comment.

comments.text: The backpack is a silent witness to this case! The backpack was found in the jungle after many weeks in perfect condition, it shows that it could not have been an accident! The backpack had to be found to stop the worldwide search! The one who put the backpack in the place by the river knows what happened to the two girls! And the biggest mistake of the backpack was that it was found in absolutely good condition! The one who put the backpack there forgot to get the backpack dirty! Rest In Peace, Kris and Lisanne! Thank you so much for this video! Have a nice day!

comments.text:
This case is fascinating, respectfully. All the theories are wild but also possible. BUT, PERSONALLY, I do believe that it was just an accident that the corrupt AND INCOMPETENT authorities managed SO BAD that in the end... the case just doesn't make sense. For example, I heard that one of the photos WAS in fact altered by authorities but it was an accident, they didn't save the original first and they brightened a photo to see better... altering the evidence. An in that way, they could have bleached the bone and then they were like "shoot, forgot to take the picture first". 

We cannot believe in any evidence. 

So, yeah, I think it was incompetence, corruption and (without a doubt) a sense of rush to close the case.
comments.author: @linchinchulin

comments.text: I wonder if you read "Still Lost in Panama'" , a book published on 2024 written by Annette Nenner & Christian Hardinghaus. They went there, and tried everything they could to get to the truth.  They list remaining questions at the back of the book. I highly recommend it. (E.g. they found out that those photos of the girls by the waterfall with 2 men, wasn't Kris and Lisanne.  The girl who was there at the waterfall, , explained that day.  Whew ! It's exhausting, but personally I follow this mystery until new info comes up. Being a woman, it scares me so much.

comments.text: From Finland... What we can learn about this? I m asking because I dont believe that this case cant find the solution anymore. Things what I have learned are for example, if you go hiking, tell someone who you trust, where you are going and when you have planned to come back. Get knowledge what kind of conditions there is. Take clothes for rein and for cold. Map and compass, phone and so on. Think water and food and take more just for case. Pocket lamp and lighter or sticks for the fire. Some first aid equipment. Dont be naive. You can meet people who look like nice but you dont really know. And for the end. Keep yourself safe and dont go over your limits. If you do even those things what I wrote, you can enjoy nature with peace. Rip Kris and Lisanne.
comments.author: @08tini

comments.text:
What keeps me awaken in the night is the question where those women have been between the first and the eight of april and why had no one seen them?
And how is it possible that a bunch of such dull bush people (authorities included) could possibly ever come up with such a rabbithole of a riddle?
The answer could only be: We are dealing with a mix of facts an poorly done madeups. But why have those not been made any better? Simply: They knew the real reasons of their deaths and it was an accident and they had to cover it. Think about it. 
Manipulating the camera would have been easy, but manipulating the phones would not. It takes a highly paid expert to do this, so they omitted it. Also with the other belongings. Insted of wearing the backpack out, they took it right from the repository and also the foot because they kept him because he identifies one of the women. They took the bones right from the graveyard, where they still are, to misslead us here.
But where have the women been in those seven days. They have not felt distressed because  of the only few attempts to make contact. I also believe that elements of the dayfotos must have been taken during this time. In my opinion all camera-photos during this time had been erased. Equally messy because it had to be cheap and quick and executable by one or two loyal people.
Is there a place where you can go with two women without they becoming suspicious for six or seven days? A place without mobilconnection but with locations worthy of two thumbs up? And if they would have to flee, because they want to work from the seventh or eight on, a location where they could have had an accident together at the same time or get lost? For me the phones indicates that they must have been alive. But where?
comments.author: @tekonwa15

comments.text: Eileen definitely knows what REALLY happened. but didn't dare say it so she ran away from there soon after and back to Germany. Well, that's a whole bunch of gangsters.
comments.author: @larsfredblom9017

comments.text: Deep down, I began to believe that this case had something to do with selling human organs (on the black market). They were both young, fit, non smokers, etc... . Unfortunately, they checked every box for people that are looking to sell human organs on the black market (and they were young, vulnerable women). There's a lot of money to be made from selling human organs (from what I hear). It just never made sense to me about the bleached bones and some of the conditions that the remains were found in.  That's really the only thing I can think of that makes some sort of sense.  The bookbag was weird and seemed like a set up. Two bras, two pairs of sunglasses, and so on. So weird.
